@startuml
title POST /api/v1/users — Create User (201 Created)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "create_user()" as View
participant "IsTeacherOrAbove" as Perm
participant "UserInputSerializer" as Serializer
participant "can_create_user()" as RoleGate
participant "identifier_in_use()" as DupCheck
participant "generate_managed\n_username()" as UsernameGen
participant "create_user_from\n_payload()" as CreateUser
database Postgres

Client -> View: POST /users\n{name: "Jane Doe", email: "jane@...",\npassword: "...", role: "ROLE_TEACHER"}\n[JWT: admin user]
View -> Perm: has_permission(request)
Perm -> Perm: is_staff? Yes
Perm --> View: True

View -> Serializer: is_valid(raise_exception=True)
Serializer --> View: validated data

View -> View: reject if "username" in request.data\n(username is system-managed)
View -> View: validate "name" present

View -> RoleGate: can_create_user(admin, TEACHER)
RoleGate -> RoleGate: admin can create\nRESEARCHER or TEACHER -> OK
RoleGate --> View: True

View -> View: role != STUDENT, email required? Yes, present

View -> DupCheck: identifier_in_use("jane@...")
DupCheck -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = 'jane@...' OR email = 'jane@...'
Postgres --> DupCheck: False
DupCheck --> View: False (available)

View -> UsernameGen: generate_managed_username("Jane Doe")
UsernameGen -> UsernameGen: normalize -> seed -> 8-char
UsernameGen -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = ?
Postgres --> UsernameGen: False (unique)
UsernameGen --> View: "janedo42"

== @transaction.atomic ==

View -> CreateUser: create_user_from_payload(\nrole=TEACHER, creator=admin)
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO app_users\n(username="janedo42", email, name, password)
Postgres --> CreateUser: User
CreateUser -> Postgres: DELETE FROM user_roles\nWHERE user_id = ?
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO user_roles\n(user_id, role=TEACHER)
CreateUser -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS teacher_profiles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> CreateUser: False
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO teacher_profiles\n(user_id)
CreateUser --> View: User

== end transaction ==

View --> Client: 201 Created\n{detail: "User created successfully"}

note over RoleGate
  **Who can create whom:**
  Admin: RESEARCHER, TEACHER
  Researcher + CREATE_TEACHER sudo: TEACHER
  Researcher + CREATE_STUDENT sudo: STUDENT
  Teacher: STUDENT only
end note
@enduml
